This really awesome photo of a kitchen with a woman and a cool painting on the wall. The woman looks very happy, so is grinning like a cheshire rat. She is North America, 1997. Hanging from the ceiling as an interesting wooden sign with the word "Upscale" carved into it. The grinning woman wears an intricate, flowerly bonnet with the bright, bold colours of the various red, yellow and blue flowers really contrasting against her jet-black hair. She has very average features, with just a single nose and two bright-blue eyes - both of which are on her face. Her armoured outfit is made of black-painted, reinforced steel-plated sheets, with an amazingly detailed rodent logo on. The painting is oil on canvas with a matte finish, and shows a heroric rat warrior wearing amazing, orange robes made of some futuristic material. The photo was proably taken in the summer of 1968 by a really amateur time-travelling photographer from the future of science fiction using a 10mp camera to keep everything in focus.
